description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you experienced in providing Complex Care to children and young people?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare is seeking experienced Support Workers to assist a young girl with her complex care needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Support Workers who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user is currently at Whiston Hospital, she needs a dedicated and compassionate care team to get her home to her family – Please note shadow shifts will take place here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A set routine is a vital part to her care as she can become very upset and anxious if this changes for any reason.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When she is at home, she enjoys baking with her mum and likes to partake in arts and crafts. She is an extremely artistic young girl and loves to draw.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would be ideal if you had experience with managing challenging behaviours and strong knowledge of autism.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 6 months previous care experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Autism Awareness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Mental Health Awareness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Managing challenging behaviours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 12 hour days&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 12 hour nights &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on her day to day life.&lt;/p&gt;
